defs.docs: Named-Pipe is a wrapper for overlapped (asyncronous) IO of Windows's named pipes.

defs.name: Read
defs.docs: Read only pipe instance

defs.name: Write
defs.docs: Write only pipe instance

defs.name: Duplex
defs.docs: Read-write pipe instance

defs.name: PipeOptions
defs.docs: Options and flags which can be used to configure how a pipe is created.

defs.name: first
defs.docs: Is this instance (or instances) will be first for this pipe name? Defaults to `true`.

defs.name: open_mode
defs.docs: Open mode for pipe instance. Defaults to `Duplex`.

defs.name: in_buffer
defs.docs: Input buffer size for pipe instance. Defaults to 65536

defs.name: out_buffer
defs.docs: Output buffer size for pipe instance. Defaults to 65536.

defs.name: single
defs.docs: Creates single instance of pipe with this options.

defs.name: multiple
defs.docs: Creates multiple instances of pipe with this options.

defs.name: ConnectingServer
defs.docs:
Pipe instance waiting for new client. Can be used with [`wait`](fn.wait.html) and [`wait_all`]
 (fn.wait_all.html) functions.

defs.name: wait
defs.docs: Waites for client infinitely.

defs.name: wait_ms
defs.value: fn (mut self, timeout: u32) -> io::Result<Result<PipeServer, ConnectingServer>>
defs.docs: Waites for client. Note that `timeout` 0xFFFFFFFF stands for infinite waiting.

defs.name: PipeServer
defs.docs: Pipe server connected to a client.

defs.name: disconnect
defs.docs:
This function will flush buffers and disconnect server from client. Then will start waiting
 for a new client.

defs.name: read_async_owned
defs.docs: Initializes asyncronous read operation and takes ownership of buffer and server.

defs.name: write_async_owned
defs.docs: Initializes asyncronous write operation and takes ownership of buffer and server.

defs.name: set_read_timeout
defs.docs: Allows you to set read timeout in milliseconds.

defs.name: set_write_timeout
defs.docs: Allows you to set write timeout in milliseconds.

defs.name: PipeClient
defs.docs: Pipe client connected to a server.

defs.name: connect
defs.docs: Will wait for server infinitely.

defs.name: connect_ms
defs.docs: Will wait for server. Note that `timeout` 0xFFFFFFFF stands for infinite waiting.

defs.name: read_async_owned
defs.docs: Initializes asyncronous read operation and takes ownership of buffer and client.

defs.name: write_async_owned
defs.docs: Initializes asyncronous write operation and takes ownership of buffer and client.

defs.name: set_read_timeout
defs.docs: Allows you to set read timeout in milliseconds.

defs.name: set_write_timeout
defs.docs: Allows you to set write timeout in milliseconds.

defs.name: PipeIo
defs.docs: This trait used for genericity.

defs.name: ReadHandle
defs.docs:
Pending read operation. Can be used with [`wait`](fn.wait.html) and [`wait_all`]
 (fn.wait_all.html) functions.

defs.name: wait
defs.docs: Will wait for completion infinitely, or until read_timeout reached if read_timeout has been set.

defs.name: WriteHandle
defs.docs:
Pending write operation. Can be used with [`wait`](fn.wait.html) and [`wait_all`]
 (fn.wait_all.html) functions.

defs.name: wait
defs.docs: Will wait for completion infinitely, or until write_timeout reached if write_timeout has been set.

defs.docs: This function will wait for first finished io operation and return it's index in `list`.
